comment: THIS is my problem with the Me Too movement. Although I support it overall, the whole "guilty until proven innocent" mentality can be utilized by abusive women like Amber to hurt innocent men. Most men don't have the money, fame, or fanbase to get the defense that Depp is getting, and even still he seems to be on the losing side of the battle. Obviously we should support those who say they've been assaulted and we should do everything we can to get justice, but that doesn't mean we should automatically believe them if it's only one or two people making allegations (like in Depp's case). Once tons of people start coming forward (like in the case of Bill Cosby or Harvey Weinstien), then that's a different story because it is substantially less likely that they are lying.

But lets not act like Johnny Depp is marriage material ok . He hasn't ever been . Johnny has a dark side he has hidden well . Take a look at his movie roles folks .They are not a stretch for him to play really . He has played Murderers , Rapists , Thieves , Drunks , Domestic Abusers , Drug Dealers , body dismemberers . Obviously Johnny is interested in those roles primarily which is pretty strange . This guy is known for being a drug and alcohol user for the last 35 years . He has boasted about drinking over 40,000 dollars worth of wine a month , on camera . That's just disgraceful . There's not just Physical abuse , there's emotional and verbal abuse . Habitual Drunks like Johnny can be verbally abusive .  Lets face it Johnny is 23 yrs older than Amber and didn't have the patience to deal with her youth . Older men are not into games . These two abused each other in some way really . Amber more physical , Johnny more verbal I believe . Say what you want but Johnny was highly drunk and acting like an erratic lunatic in Amber's video of him at home slamming cabinet doors , fiending for alchohol . Why would he destroy her phone on camera on this occassion if he is the victim ? He obviously didn't want to be exposed . Johnny cant or hasn't explained that instance . What sane woman would put up with a drunken man like this everyday ? Of course every Hollywood actor Johnny knows would defend him in on how they see his public image he presents . This guy is a payed actor folks . Joan Crawford was a respected lady in public , and a lunatic tyrant child abuser at home . So no one really knows someone fully . The way Johnny acted at home in that video with Amber is probably why Vanessa left him , and how he can be at times whether his fans , friends , or associates like it or not . The simple facts are every fiance , GF , or wife has left him over 35 years for unknown reasons . The guy cant keep a woman obviously no matter how appealing he might seem , and nobody agknowledges that fact  . 

The conclusion is I believe is that Johnny had been highly jealous of the Brangelina phenominon . How Brad and Angelina were 12 years apart in age , how they met on a movie set romanticly , how Brad got her to have biological kids , and then they became the King and Queen of Hollywood overnight being together . Johnny was fascinated on How Amber and Angelina are / were young bisexual women untamed by a man and family life . Johnny wanted to replicate on Amber how Brad tamed Angelina that way . So Johnny met Amber on a movie set who is 23 years younger than him . He got with her and married her . The trouble is Johnny wanted to make a biological family with Amber , and she never had that intention unfortunately . Johnny was a short term stepping stone for her ambitions , and it worked briefly . Amber and Johnny were not compatable long term . Amber has said she is fiercely independant , and not a homebody really . She is clearly more into happy go lucky fun loving strong tall man's man kinda guys like Jason Momoa . Lets face it , Johnny has a more feminity about him that Amber soured on eventually . Amber was the man and Johnny was the woman in this failed relationship really . The respect level dis-intigrates if the woman takes on the man's role mentally in a relationship . .

comment:
People can be all bunch of good things publicly when interacting with strangers, friends, children but when with one's self or their very most intimate other ,behind closed door, while no one is looking , other hidden not so good qualities may lash out !
.
.
Good or bad is a judgment you make on others majorly by true little things you know about them genuinely doing in their normal day-to-day life, which even then remains faulty cause some people can be very good in concealment. That way of judgment is even harder to do on celebrities because all aspects of their life is almost a public record, microscopically scrutinized by people; therefore who they really are - or what are genuinely like - is hard to be conclusively decided based on what they show and exhibit to the public.
.
.
All conclusions and testimonies by JD's friends and family are theoretical and derivative from who and what they have know JD to be like; #ButWhatIf there is a darker side about the man they haven't been introduced to. Maybe Some behavioural or psychotic mental disorder he developed in the recent years of his life??

Let's keep in mind that between the two, JD is the man and has more years of experience, much more than that in wealth, and connections therefore he is rather more intimidating to - and/or respected by- others even so to/by the younger "abusive" wife. JD is an accomplished man who  has lived, seen and done alot ; him pulling off this as a ascheme (fooling the whole world and victimizing himself when he really is the perpetrator) to feel the intoxicating sensation behind it can be a very probable motive. 

On the other hand, Talking about motive, we have Amber! the younger still under accomplished wife who is looking forward to jump-start her acting career into stardom !!  assuming she is an "abusive" person, wouldn't it be more beneficial and practical for her to choose controlling her urge of practicing violence and holding it in- or direct it towards any thing/one else- rather than hitting her husband (knowing all who He is and all he can do) and then filling a law suit against him?.

Sorry Folks ! I just don't feel comfortable passing judgment and automatically verdicting on this case based on released phone calls recordings, trended #es, bias opinion I have about an icon celebrity influenced by his/her fame and/or what others are saying about him/her.

#JustSaying

comment: I love how everyone is telling everyone about Johnny's behavior and past. I just gottasay this. I dated a guy everyone said was great,funny blah blah. But within one year of us being together,his behavior changed but it was also me having issues too. Not saying exactly what things were done but I know that my ex said they were never this way with any of his ex's. Now I'm not defending amber bc ive seen a lot and heard a lot and I'm really team depp anyway. But all it really takes is one crazy fit of range when you won't leave someone alone and that tends to get physical. The guy tried to seperate you from him so the pushing shoving and locking the door on yyou is a way of separating oneself from conflict in a way to descalate the situation. Its funny like ironic how this comes up bc literally this morning there was an incident outside of the building I was at which woke me. I was sleeping over a friends place helping them clean up ect. When I hear a woman yelling for someone to open the back door. But I'll tell u how this pertains to depps behavior.ok so the woman can't get it.shes wearing sweats and short sleeve no shoes or coat. Its alittle chilly but not too cold. She can't get it so she opened the back window which is a bedroom on the 1st florr where her man was sleeping. She started yelling at him to open up how shes got no shoes blah blah but when he didnt open the door,trying to get her to leave she became increasingly irritated. After about 30 minutes of her pushing up against the window, him pushing her back out while shes attempting to climb in ,he's yelling at her to get out and leave him alone he placed hers shoes out on the winddow with a coat/sweater but no she didnt want that. So shes going to the next window which I think is an empty bedroom or something. So the girl gets in thru that  window and begins to bang on the door from the inside. I assume he had it locked. Then she starts screaming bloody murder. Things like this happen all the time when drug activity /or homelessness couples pair up ive seen it with neighbors. Now my point was this guy was separated from her. She wouldn't leave him alone and that caused him to snap. I admit I was crazy like that with my daughter and my son making sure their father would come home if he was out at the bar,or next door or wherever if I had to work or if I didnt trust him being out drinking with people which I always was crazy jealous like that and usually that was my fight starter. I didnt think a guy should drink out with other women even if hes with guys. (Later I found out he cheated on me with one of these women but anyway). My point for this was I used to believe that if in any situation of d.v, even with my parents fighting over cheating spouses in a separation/divorce, they would always arrest my father even when ive seen my mother putting her hands on him. comment:
The truth is still the truth... in that crazy boy toys, do in fact actually drive their significant others coocoo. At some point, a female clues into her reality of infidelity; lies; and narcissism. These are very real truths about being a male whom, does not or cannot settle in or commit to one attentive relationship.
In fact, the heart throb is someone many ppl envy.  But the outcomes of continually being groomed in this manner from a young age. These are the risks to in turn pursue women of the same backgrounds.
Women whom are emotionally charged without moral directive as a youth, easily misinterpret their own beliefs and personal experiences.  The hope in these situations, is that only life in maturity can teach the more average individual. Where men, whom can and do have any women they want.  Can of sorts, 'wake up', and thus appreciate a more stable lifestyle. It is tragic, that women tend to be at higher risk, to re-establish stability. Even than, the actual re-establishinv of psychological restructuring.  Is very intense and thoroughly guaranteed.
Therefore, if any child cannot or does not have proper parenting in place before hand, the cycles of inaccuracy are often much too overwhelming,  to overcome. So, whatever tragedies there are in inheritance, in even generations beforehand. The capacity to changes these or recognize them are very minimal.
As a First Nation Canadian mother, I myself stay hopeful... I advocate from a family level. And I under took the psychological changes that I needed, in order to thrive. I see the adversity firsthand against my children. And my reasoning for not conforming to unhealthy people, is commonly despised. Thankfully, for myself, I grew up with a sense of reasoning compassion and wisdom for right and wrong. Where, I have been able to seemingly avoid direct dysfunctions and keep a clear perspective about truth.
In contrast to this however, I do in fact suffer immensely with isolation effects. I dont have very severe symptoms of doubt. But now that I have matured, I do question my motives of vanity in opposition to family violence. So technically, I have similar struggles to which I do in fact identify.  Where vanity as an onset, does play a role in my capacity to cope. Which, in contrast, my own reasoning for companionship is from the second nature of my family life struggles.
I, commit very devotingly to a healthy and safe home, for my children. Where the only true saving grace, that I can believe in, is in fact the truth.  When people are abusive, and tend to blame and lie, rather than interpretion themselves in the situation.  It just seems more protective and humane, to speak about problems from beginning to end, with healthy outcomes as the benefactor. I feel like, if my children learnwhy it is important to choose the right. Than the possibilities of firgiveness and in meeting good people in the world. Is their best allie. I dont know what the mental health risks are for, the very real levels of disruption that I have been living with, along side unwell family members. 
It actually seems horrifying. And I think this is another area where, even my children knowing the reality of human life at home, in the family. Are better than living at risk. Thinking that ppl and life situations are normal, when they are not.
As our own family unit. We stay hopeful through volunteering and donating food to the essential workers, whom spend a lot of time away from their own homes and families.
We have a little area of loving appreciation from the faces in the community we often see.and its so nice to bting that light in their smiles, when they see us! I am never short of conversations to revelate my belonging.
Perhaps one day, I can at least forgive the anger and unwellness in my own upbringing, that I am unable to allow in my own life.
My parents have been separated since I was 3, I am the product of the end of their first marriages and former families. My father continued on with addictional relationships and children. Where his life long struggle with depression and racism, ended within the dis-unity of his own home, where his health complications were far beyond manageable.
I have always been deeply in love with my dad, and my siblings, to which I find the truth much more soothing to know the reality of the problematic circumstances by which I struggle with. I know God is real, and I do not blame the Father son and the Holy Spirit üíú Thank you.

comment:
What Johnny Depp did wrong and needs to fix.  He let amber Heard into his life and potentially around his kids.  If she was willing to do the things alleged about her to Johnny than she would also be willing to do them to his kids.  This is something no real man should tolerate.  feminist say that the rule should be strike one and your out, well, that should go both ways.  People need to realize that it isn't about a strength difference between two people, but the strength difference between either of them and a CHILD!  Men should not tolerate a threat to their children and violent abusive women are a threat to the man's children.  No relationship exist in a vacuum and how two people relate to one another has much further impact than just the two of them.  This is the true horror of domestic violence.  Johnny Depp failed as a father if he let Amber Heard be around his kids.  As a man this is something I definitely hold Johnny Depp responsible for.

It should be noted that at no point did I take Amber's 'side'.  She is even worse, but there is more than enough blame to go around.  It is simply that I always side with the kids and in my opinion domestic violence should be evaluated based on how each partner's conduct would effect a child in their home.  I call it the third party rule.  This is why domestic violence situations are never a she versus he thing.  Everyone how ignores the impact of domestic violence on other people are guilty of ignoring how it effects children, police officers, neighbors, other member's of the family.  Everyone who thinks domestic violence is what men do to women shows a profound lack of concern over the health and wellbeing of children and are just interested in continuing the abuse.
